d back and beyond. David Farrell Krell retraces the journeys in striking detail, reflecting on their significance for Hölderlin's life and work in ways that will interest a wide swath of fellow thinkers and travelers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aPoets, Germany19th centuryvBiography. 4aArea Studies : German Studies. 4aGeneral Interest : Poetry. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aLiterature : Romanticism. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPsychology : Psychology. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849504040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438495040423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438495040/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles